===Etymology 1===
<div style="float:right;">
{{wp|ja:プレアデス星団}}
{{wp|Pleiades}}
</div>
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|すばる}}

Likely from {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=すばる|-}}, use of kanji in Japanese texts first appears in the ''{{w|ja:丹後国風土記|Tango-no-kuni Fudoki}}'' (''c.'' mid-8th century), phonetic spelling first attested in the ''{{w|Wamyō Ruijushō}}'' (938 {{CE}}).

By extension from {{m|ja|統ばる|tr=subaru||to [[bunch]] together; to [[unite]]|pos=intransitive}}, due to the way the [[star]]s in the [[constellation]] all ''[[cluster]]'' together.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR"/> Compare {{m|ja|統べる|tr=suberu||to [[command]]|pos=transitive}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|すばる|acc=1|acc_ref=DJR}}

====Proper noun====
{{ja-pos|proper|すばる}}

# {{lb|ja|astronomy|sort=すばる}} the [[Pleiades]] [[star cluster]], one of the {{w|Twenty-Eight Mansions}}
#: {{synonyms|ja|プレアデス星団|tr=Pureadesu-seidan|昴宿|tr2=Bōshuku|昴星|tr3=Subaruboshi, Bōsei|六連星|tr4=Mutsuraboshi}}
# {{given name|ja|female|sort=すばる}}

